A simple keylogger, developed for XMonad screencasting.

To build:
  $ ./bootstrap.sh
  $ ./configure
  $ make

To run:
  $ cd src
  # ./keylog [-d /dev/input/eventX] [-m keymap.txt]

To find keyboard device:
  $ grep -w sysrq /proc/bus/input/devices

If that one doesn't work, try all the kbd devices...
  $ grep -w kbd /proc/bus/input/devices

To create a custom keymap:
  $ cd src
  $ rm keymap.txt
  $ make keymap.txt
  # showkey
  $ vi keymap.txt

